    General resources:

  • https://huggingface.co/models - online platform where researchers and AI enthusiasts upload models that can compete with big tech companies
  • https://www.kaggle.com/ - online community platform of data scientists that hosts challenges and provides a free Jupyter notebook environment
  • https://colab.research.google.com/ - free Jupyter notebook environment (preferable to Kaggle)
  • https://paperswithcode.com/ - aggregates code from state-of-the-art research papers
  • https://datasetsearch.research.google.com/ - dataset search
  • https://research.google/resources/datasets/ - google’s released datasets

Specific resources:

  • https://pytorch-geometric.readthedocs.io/en/latest/ - library for graph neural networks
  • https://moody-challenge.physionet.org/ - data science challenges related to ECGs and other physiological signals
  • https://pharmapsychotic.com/tools.html - list of AI art tools
  • https://gymnasium.farama.org/ - Python library for creating reinforcement learning environments
  • https://developers.google.com/earth-engine/datasets - google earth engine

    Helpful channels:

  • Stanford CS231 (website: http://cs231n.stanford.edu/)
  • MIT 6.S191 (website: http://introtodeeplearning.com/)
  • Aleksa Gordić - The AI Epiphany
  • TwoMinutePapers
  • Yannic Kilcher
  • Outlier
